102
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:04,760
Wow, impressive!

103
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:07,640
It's the surfer, Amuro!

104
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:11,000
She'll go to America
three days later for a world tour,

105
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:15,440
but she agreed readily to be
his coach if it's just one day.

106
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:17,480
So cool!

107
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:23,240
I want to take this photo.

108
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:27,680
I think it'll be rather difficult.

109
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:29,160
- Obviously.
- Yes.

110
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:32,520
Waves rarely form "tubes" in the sea
in the first place,

111
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:35,640
