to learn this technique.

112
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:38,320
But we're at a wave pool this time.

113
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:41,640
It can create a wave that forms
a tube anytime freely,

114
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,640
so it depends on
how much effort Nakaoka makes.

115
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:47,680
First, he'll practise
with simple waves.

116
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:48,680
No!

117
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:50,840
But there's a small problem.

118
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:52,600
My feet can't touch the bottom.

119
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:54,960
-You have to paddle.
- This is bad.

120
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:57,840
The water is six metres deep
where the wave is,

121
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,360
and his feet can't reach the bottom.

122
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:00,440
Also...

123
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:01,360
Paddle!

124
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:05,800
It was the one just now.

125
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:08,120
It's much higher than Kobe's waves!

126
00:05:08,960 --> 00:05:13,520
It uses air pressure sent from
the pool's bottom to create waves,

127
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:15,800
