and difficulty.

151
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,720
Everyone, this is Nakaoka!

152
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:25,040
I think you often see surfers
riding white waves,

153
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:29,560
but they're broken waves
that beginners ride on.

154
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:34,440
Skilled surfers ride on the face
of a wave, which is at an angle.

155
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:37,520
Manoeuvres are possible
only after you can ride on these.

156
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:40,360
This is very difficult!

157
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:43,280
Impressive!

158
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:46,520
He starts practising again
30 minutes later.

159
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:50,360
It was Amuro's kindness
that became his support.

160
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,520
Almost!

161
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,440
She never denies his effort
and helps him improve by praises.

162
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:00,160
This is fun.

163
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:03,400
Nakaoka has gotten back
into the swing of it.

164
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:07,680
Oh, you did it... Wow!

165
00:07:08,760 --> 00:07:09,840
You made it!

166
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,320
That one was perfect.

167
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:14,440
- It was perfect?
- Yes, perfect.

168
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:18,200
I think it was a pass among today's.

169
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:20,320
What's the most important point?

170
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:21,320
It's paddling.

171
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,520
It's the most important in surfing.

172
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,440
It's paddle.

173
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:27,560
How is the paddling of a pro
different?

174
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:31,240
